Chapter 6: Build a Property Tax and Deadline Calendar
Core Question
What deadlines could harm property if missed?
Understand
Many property losses begin with missed dates.
Tax deadlines.
Insurance renewals.
Lease renewals.
Permit deadlines.
Court dates.
Probate deadlines.
Appeal deadlines.
Assessment notices.
Repair deadlines.
Code compliance dates.
A society can help members prepare by creating a property calendar.
The calendar should not expose private details.
It can track general reminders:
Property tax due month
 Homestead exemption deadline
 Insurance renewal check
 Estate document review month
 Lease renewal reminder
 Winterization reminder
 Storm prep reminder
 Code compliance education
 Local budget or development meetings
A calendar turns surprise into preparation.
Discuss
What property deadlines matter in our area?
What deadlines do people often miss?
What reminders would help without exposing personal details?
Who should maintain the calendar?
How often should reminders go out?
