Chapter 7: Create a Home Repair and Maintenance Map
Core Question
What small repairs could become big losses if ignored?
Understand
Deferred maintenance can become property loss.
A small roof leak becomes structural damage.
A plumbing issue becomes mold.
A broken step becomes injury.
Electrical problems become safety risks.
Unaddressed repairs may affect insurance, code compliance, property value, elder safety, or family stability.
A society can help by mapping repair needs, identifying trusted contractors, organizing volunteer repair days where appropriate, connecting members to grants or programs, and teaching maintenance basics.
But repair work requires care.
Do not send unqualified volunteers into dangerous work.
Do not expose elder homes publicly.
Do not promise repairs the society cannot complete.
Start with mapping, triage, referrals, and safe support.
Discuss
What repair needs repeat?
Which repairs affect elder safety?
Which repairs require licensed professionals?
Which repairs could volunteers safely help with?
Who knows trusted contractors?
What repair needs could become a care team project?
