PART THREE: EDUCATE FOR STEWARDSHIP

Chapter 9: Teach Property Basics
Core Question
What does every member need to understand before property pressure arrives?
Understand
Property education should not begin when crisis begins.
Members need basic literacy around:
Deeds
 Titles
 Mortgages
 Property taxes
 Insurance
 Wills
 Trusts
 Probate
 Heirs property
 Liens
 Code violations
 Assessments
 Appraisals
 Leases
 Commercial leases
 Tenant rights
 Home maintenance
 Predatory lending
 Development pressure
 Zoning
 Community land ownership
 Cooperatives
 Community land trusts
The society does not need to teach everything at once.
Choose one property education topic based on your vulnerability map.
Education should produce action.
After a workshop, members should know what document to locate, what question to ask, what deadline to check, or what professional to contact.
Discuss
What property topic confuses people most?
What topic connects to a real risk?
Who can teach or refer?
What action should members take after learning?
How will we protect privacy during discussion?
