PART FOUR: PREPARE FOR OWNERSHIP

Chapter 13: Create a Property Readiness Score
Core Question
Are we ready to pursue property, or do we need more preparation?
Understand
A society should not rush into ownership because property sounds powerful.
Property can strengthen a society.
It can also overwhelm it.
Before pursuing property, ask:
Do we have clear governance?
Do we have treasury discipline?
Do we have clean records?
Do we have decision rules?
Do we have conflict repair?
Do we understand legal structures?
Do we have professional guidance?
Do we have maintenance capacity?
Do we have reserve funds?
Do we understand risk?
Do we know what the property is for?
Do we have a plan for stewardship?
A building can become a blessing or a burden.
Readiness matters.
Discuss
Why do we want property?
What would property allow us to do?
What would property require from us?
What risks are we underestimating?
What must be true before we pursue ownership?
