Chapter 15: Build the Stewardship Plan
Core Question
Who will care for the property after acquisition or protection?
Understand
Ownership is not the finish line.
Stewardship is the work after ownership.
A stewardship plan should answer:
Who maintains it?
Who pays bills?
Who schedules repairs?
Who holds keys?
Who approves use?
Who handles insurance?
Who tracks taxes?
Who reports income and expenses?
Who resolves conflicts?
Who reviews safety?
Who protects records?
Who trains youth?
Who makes sure the property serves the mission?
Property can become a burden if stewardship is unclear.
A society should prepare stewardship before acquisition, not after.
Discuss
What responsibilities would property create?
Who has capacity to manage them?
What professional support is needed?
What reserve is needed?
What rules would protect use?
How will youth learn stewardship?
