Chapter 17: Property and Stewardship Report
Core Question
What did we protect, prepare, repair, or learn?
Understand
The Property and Stewardship Report is evidence.
It should not expose private ownership details.
It should show patterns and progress.
A good report may say:
We held one Property Records Day.
Twelve members completed document checklists.
Three families identified missing deed or tax records.
Two elders received private support.
One youth group completed a community space map.
Five members attended property tax education.
One repair referral list was created.
One property readiness score was completed.
No private ownership details were shared publicly.
The report should make stewardship visible while protecting people.
