Final question:
Can we protect what we already have, prepare for what we may own, and steward land across generations?

Closing Principle
Property is not only ownership.
It is responsibility across time.
A house can hold sacrifice.
A church can hold memory.
A vacant lot can hold possibility.
A deed can protect a family.
A missing document can threaten one.
A tax bill can become a crisis.
A trusted record can become defense.
A young person who understands stewardship can become the future guardian of what others built.
The work is not only to acquire.
The work is to protect.
To document.
To educate.
To repair.
To prepare.
To steward.
Land is time made visible.
Treat it like memory with an address.

